{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-vows-4000-8000-projectvows001",
    "name": "Project Vows API",
    "description": "Wedding invitation & WhatsApp RSVP backend (Gin + GORM + MySQL, Twilio WhatsApp).\n\n## Setup\nImport this collection together with `ProjectVows.postman_environment.json` and select the **Project Vows - Local** environment.\n\nEnvironment variables:\n- `base_url`        : e.g. http://localhost:8080\n- `tag`             : event tag, e.g. stanley-arum\n- `event_id`        : captured automatically by *Events > Create event*\n- `invitation_id`   : captured automatically by *Invitations > List invitations* (first item)\n- `invitation_id_2` : captured automatically by *Invitations > List invitations* (second item)\n- `qr_code_token`   : captured automatically by *Invitations > List invitations* (first item)\n\n## Response envelope\nEvery JSON endpoint returns:\n```json\n{ \"status\": \"success|error\", \"message\": \"...\", \"data\": {}, \"error\": \"machine_code\" }\n```\n\n## Suggested run order\n1. Health > Health check\n2. Events > Create event\n3. Invitations > Import guests (CSV) — select docs/sample_guests.csv\n4. Invitations > List invitations (captures ids + qr token)\n5. WhatsApp Send > Send invitations (by id)\n6. (simulate RSVP complete in DB) WhatsApp Send > Generate & send QR\n7. Check-in > Look up guest by QR\n8. Check-in > Check in\n\n## Notes\n- WhatsApp sending uses **Twilio**. Sends require `TWILIO_*` env vars on the server; otherwise send endpoints return per-item failures with reason \"twilio is not configured\".\n- QR delivery is **stateless**: the QR image is generated in memory on demand and served at `GET /qr/:qr_code_token` (nothing is stored). Twilio fetches that URL as media.\n- The WhatsApp webhook is **Twilio** (form-encoded POST authenticated via `X-Twilio-Signature`). There is no Meta-style GET verification handshake.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Liveness probe. Returns `{\"status\":\"ok\"}`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Events",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create event",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json && json.data && json.data.id) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('event_id', json.data.id);",
                  "  if (json.data.tag) { pm.environment.set('tag', json.data.tag); }",
                  "  console.log('Captured event_id =', json.data.id);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('status is 2xx', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([200, 201]);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tag\": \"{{tag}}\",\n  \"couple_name\": \"Stanley & Arum\",\n  \"holy_matrimony_date\": \"2026-09-12T09:00:00Z\",\n  \"holy_matrimony_location\": \"St. Mary Church, Jakarta\",\n  \"reception_date\": \"2026-09-12T18:00:00Z\",\n  \"reception_location\": \"Grand Ballroom, Jakarta\",\n  \"gift_address\": \"Jl. Melati No. 1, Jakarta\",\n  \"bank_account\": \"BCA 1234567890 a/n Stanley\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/events",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "events"]
            },
            "description": "Create a wedding event. `tag` and `couple_name` are required; all date/location/gift fields are optional. On success returns the created event (201). Duplicate tag returns 409 `create_failed`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List events",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/events",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "events"]
            },
            "description": "List all events."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get event by id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/events/{{event_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "events", "{{event_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Fetch a single event by numeric id. 404 `event_not_found` if missing."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Invitations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Import guests (CSV)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "CSV with header `tag,guest_name,whatsapp_number`. Use docs/sample_guests.csv."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/import-csv",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "import-csv"]
            },
            "description": "Multipart upload (form field `file`). Header row `tag,guest_name,whatsapp_number` is auto-detected. Each row is validated independently; failures are returned in `data.failed_rows` without aborting the import. The referenced event `tag` must already exist."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List invitations",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "const rows = (json && json.data) || [];",
                  "if (rows.length > 0) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('invitation_id', rows[0].id);",
                  "  if (rows[0].qr_code_token) { pm.environment.set('qr_code_token', rows[0].qr_code_token); }",
                  "  console.log('Captured invitation_id =', rows[0].id, 'qr_code_token =', rows[0].qr_code_token);",
                  "}",
                  "if (rows.length > 1) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('invitation_id_2', rows[1].id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations?tag={{tag}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "tag", "value": "{{tag}}" },
                { "key": "event_id", "value": "", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "rsvp_status", "value": "attending", "description": "not_answered | attending | not_attending", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "invitation_status", "value": "invitation_sent", "description": "imported | invitation_sent | invitation_failed", "disabled": true }
              ]
            },
            "description": "List invitations with optional filters: `tag`, `event_id`, `rsvp_status`, `invitation_status`. (There is no `qr_status` filter — QR delivery is stateless and stores no QR state.)"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get invitation by id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/{{invitation_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "{{invitation_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Fetch a single invitation (with event + check-in logs) by id. 404 `invitation_not_found` if missing."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "WhatsApp Send",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Send invitations (by id)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"ids\": [{{invitation_id}}],\n  \"image_url\": \"https://example.com/invitation-card.jpg\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/send",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "send"]
            },
            "description": "Send the initial invitation to the given invitation ids. Updates `invitation_status` to `invitation_sent`/`invitation_failed` and writes a `whatsapp_logs` row per send. Returns a batch summary.\n\n`image_url` (optional): a publicly reachable HTTPS image attached to the invitation (Twilio fetches it as WhatsApp media). Omit or leave empty for a text-only message. Ignored when an approved Content Template SID is configured on the server."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Send pending (by tag)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tag\": \"{{tag}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/send-pending",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "send-pending"]
            },
            "description": "Send the initial invitation to all imported (not-yet-sent) guests of a tag."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Resend unanswered (by tag)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tag\": \"{{tag}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/resend-unanswered",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "resend-unanswered"]
            },
            "description": "Resend the invitation to guests whose `rsvp_status` is still `not_answered`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Send reminder (by tag)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tag\": \"{{tag}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/send-reminder",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "send-reminder"]
            },
            "description": "Send a reminder to all attending guests of a tag."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Generate & send QR (by tag)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tag\": \"{{tag}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/generate-send-qr",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "generate-send-qr"]
            },
            "description": "For each eligible guest (rsvp_status = attending, pax_count not null, event_choice not null): generate a QR in memory and send it via WhatsApp (Twilio fetches the on-demand `/qr/:qr_code_token` URL). Nothing is stored. Writes a `send_qr` `whatsapp_logs` row. Note: stateless delivery has no 'already sent' gate — repeated calls re-send."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Resend QR (by tag + ids)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"tag\": \"{{tag}}\",\n  \"ids\": [{{invitation_id}}]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/invitations/resend-qr",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "invitations", "resend-qr"]
            },
            "description": "Resend a fresh QR to selected invitation ids (guarded to the given tag). Every resend regenerates a new QR in memory and sends immediately; nothing is reused or persisted. Writes a `resend_qr` `whatsapp_logs` row."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "QR Image",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get QR image (PNG)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/qr/{{qr_code_token}}.png",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["qr", "{{qr_code_token}}.png"]
            },
            "description": "Public, stateless QR image endpoint. Generates the QR PNG in memory on demand (encoding the check-in URL) and streams it as `image/png`. This is the URL Twilio fetches as WhatsApp media. The `.png` suffix is optional. 404 `invitation_not_found` for an unknown token."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Webhook (Twilio)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Webhook probe (GET)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/webhook/whatsapp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "webhook", "whatsapp"]
            },
            "description": "Twilio does not use a GET verification handshake (unlike Meta). This endpoint simply returns 200 `ok` for health/probing."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Inbound message (POST)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" },
              { "key": "X-Twilio-Signature", "value": "", "description": "Set by Twilio. When TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN is configured on the server, the signature is validated and mismatches return 403 invalid_signature." }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "MessageSid", "value": "SM00000000000000000000000000000000" },
                { "key": "From", "value": "whatsapp:+6281234567890" },
                { "key": "To", "value": "whatsapp:+14155238886" },
                { "key": "Body", "value": "Hadir" },
                { "key": "ProfileName", "value": "Budi Santoso" },
                { "key": "NumMedia", "value": "0" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/webhook/whatsapp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "webhook", "whatsapp"]
            },
            "description": "Twilio inbound WhatsApp message (application/x-www-form-urlencoded). The sender is resolved by `From` (whatsapp:+E164); when matched, an inbound `whatsapp_logs` row is written. Unknown senders are ignored. Returns 200 `{\"status\":\"received\"}`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Status callback (POST)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" },
              { "key": "X-Twilio-Signature", "value": "", "description": "Set by Twilio; validated when TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN is configured." }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "MessageSid", "value": "SM00000000000000000000000000000000" },
                { "key": "MessageStatus", "value": "delivered", "description": "queued | sending | sent | delivered | read | failed | undelivered" },
                { "key": "To", "value": "whatsapp:+6281234567890" },
                { "key": "From", "value": "whatsapp:+14155238886" }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/webhook/whatsapp",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "webhook", "whatsapp"]
            },
            "description": "Twilio delivery/status callback. A payload containing `MessageStatus` updates the matching outbound `whatsapp_logs` row's status (failed/undelivered → failed; sent/delivered/read → sent; else pending)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Check-in",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Look up guest by QR",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/check-in/{{qr_code_token}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "check-in", "{{qr_code_token}}"]
            },
            "description": "Resolve a guest by QR token and return guest name, pax count, event choice, and per-event check-in status. 404 `invitation_not_found` for an unknown token."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Check in",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"qr_code_token\": \"{{qr_code_token}}\",\n  \"event_type\": \"holy_matrimony\",\n  \"actual_pax\": 2,\n  \"scanner_name\": \"Gate A\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/check-in",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "check-in"]
            },
            "description": "Record a check-in. `event_type` is `holy_matrimony` or `reception` (must be allowed by the guest's `event_choice`). `actual_pax` must be >= 1 and <= registered `pax_count`. Errors: 404 `invitation_not_found`, 422 `not_attending`/`invalid_event`/`invalid_pax`, 409 `already_checked_in`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8080" },
    { "key": "tag", "value": "stanley-arum" }
  ]
}
